title: 820-00840 (Q7900 Failure)   Now missing P5S4_EN
message:
Well the good news is that it was Q7900 that was shorted and not Q8060.  Maybe the CPU survived.
I checked all the CPU power rails resistance against my two answer keys "working boards" and they were similar.

After replacing Q7900 I now have PPBUS_G3H back. 
However I am missing my P5S4_EN at U7650

Once I get into U7800 I am pretty much lost. 
This is not a water damaged board.   Initial failure was Q7900 so I am guessing I have a PCH problem here!

PMIC_SHUTDOWN_L 3.3v
PP3V1 _RTC 3.1V
SMC_LRESET_L 0.0v
PM_SYSRST_L 3.3v
S5_PWRGD 3.2v

I am really kind of lost here.

RTC_RESET_L 3.1v
SYSCLK_CLK32_PCH "nice square wave"
PCH_SUSACK_L 3.2

yea... I am lost
